description:
Grunge and Roxy watch a Hong Kong action film festival, inspiring Grunge to create his own action film.

Claiming that storylines are not critical in the current state of the film industry, Grunge makes up a plot for his film and describes it to Roxy, complete with product placement and mis-translations:

A Swordsman and his sidekick "Kiddo" (played by Grunge and Roxy) return to their village in historical China and find the villagers (played by Bobby and Sarah) massacred. They are attacked by the forces of the government (played by the DV8 team).

Grunge and Roxy are outnumbered and seemingly defeated by DV8, when they are rescued by a Shaolin warrior monk (played by Caitlin). With Caitlin's aid, Grunge and Roxy defeat DV8. Grunge discovers that the DV8 team is working for a villain known as "T.H.E.B.I.G.B.O.S!"
name: Grunge The Movie, Part. 1

description:
Roxy comments that Grunge's movie has, so far, been one scene of mindless violence.

Grunge responds by including unconnected love scenes inspired by "chick flicks" and by raunchier fare.

In Grunge's imaginary movie:

Grunge, Roxy, and Caitlin are attacked by agents of The Big Boss (played by the WildC.A.T.s, Wetworks, Deathblow and Stormwatch.) The three defeat their enemies in a series of gun battles referencing Quentin Tarantino films.
name: Grunge The Movie, Part. 2

description: The movie concludes with Grunge as the star battling T.H.E. B.I.G. B.O.S.S. who turns out to be Lynch. Grunge narrates his epically heroic and awesome drunk stylized finishing fight moves well after Lynch overtakes Farichild and Freefall with toy race car tracks (?). The goofball gags run amuck like Grunge's imagination, but heck you can only predict the silliness that ends after the credits roll.
name: Grunge The Movie, Part. 3

description: Rowdy fistfights with villains on the beach would raise the ire of any neighbor. Fortunately the Gen13 crew makes friends, eventually, with their closest neighbors, saving them from danger. The kids end up filling a childless void in the couple's life.

Scared-Of Love

The young in heart are never old, but the old in heart are never young... and Ann's heart had closed upon the carefree joy of being young, upon the very Springtime of life.

But then she met Mark, and in his arms she found a Second Spring.

Wanted: The Perfect Man

Some people go through life chasing rainbows... rainbows they can never catch. Such a person was Marge. Unable to be happy with anyone because she was overly-critical, intolerant of even the smallest thing, Marge chased the rainbow of perfection. But even she never thought things would turn out as they did when she finally found... Her Perfect Man

The Happiness and Heartbreak of Vicki Carter Chapter III: Love's Sacrifice (Text Only Story)

Betrayed By My Temper

With hair like hers, Ginger thought she couldn't help it if she had a temper. The fiery nature that made her explode at trifles-- was part and parcel of her eager joy in love, Ginger insisted.

It wasn't till losing her temper lost her love-- that she learned the full price of being a terrible-tempered Redhead!

I Led Him On

In love with one man, Betty encouraged another to give her his heart, leading him on and all the while telling herself she did no wrong. But she learned the bitter lesson that for everything taken, there must someday be an accounting!

Disillusioned

When darkness and gloom are the handmaidens of the heart, the world is a cheerless place. So it was with Joan, who could see but one side of everything--the unpleasant side! She saw in life only the dismal and the sombre! No wonder, then, that when love came, it found a barren heart!

Merry-Go-Round Romance

Julie was determined never to be found sitting at home, wanting for dates. She collected men as other people collect stamps, the more the better.

Then came the day she met Dan and decided to add him to her collection. But love stepped in and her own broken heart became her last... Collector's Item!

The Happiness and Heartbreak of Vicki Carter Chapter IV: The Searching Heart (Text Only Story)

I Wanted Sympathy!

How well Mary knew that sympathy is first-cousin to romance. It was a knowledge she'd made good use of all her life...... it was her road to man's heart! So it was no wonder that when she met Greg, she tried all the things that had never failed her before.

They didn't fail her this time either, but she learned that love that is founded on deceit, must someday crumble of itself!

Too Flighty For Love

To some people, the grass is always greener on the other side of the fence. So it was to Holly; pert, vivacious Holly, with the auburn heir and hazel eyes.

But one day she learned that this is not always so, an those hazel eyes came to know bitter tears --as love walked out!
